          "text": "**'I will consecrate... I will dwell... they shall know'** — the chapter's three-fold covenant climax. The shift to first-person divine declaration marks the transition from prescription to promise. All the human ritual of vv. 1-43 converges on three divine acts: consecration, dwelling, and disclosure."
