    "intro": "Application is where the text of Exodus 29 becomes a mirror held up to the reader's life — not as ancient liturgy safely contained in history, but as a word that addresses the present. The questions below are not rhetorical. They require specific, honest answers tied to real situations. Christ has fulfilled what Aaron's ordination anticipated, and the Holy Spirit has made every believer a temple. The implications are not abstract.",
